[[Image:Barabinsk steppe.jpg|right|thumb|300px|'''Baraba steppe''' as seen from the window of the [[Trans-Siberian railway]].]]
[[Image:Западная Сибирь.jpg|right|thumb|300px|Map of the '''Baraba steppe''']]

The '''Baraba steppe''', also known as '''Barabinsk steppe''', '''Barabinskaya steppe''' {{Lang-ru|Барабинская низменность}}, is a [[grassland]] [[steppe]] and wooded flat plain situated in western [[Siberia]].

The steppe has an area of 117,000&nbsp;km² and stretches between the [[Irtysh]] and the [[Ob River]]s. [[Barabinsk]] is the largest city on the steppe.  The Baraba steppe also contains an important [[Russia]]n agricultural district.

{{coord|55.7|78.0|type:landmark_dim:300km_region:RU|display=title}}

