{{further|Nesaea (alga)}}

'''Nesaea''' was one of the [[Nereids]] who gathered round [[Thetis]] in her sympathetic grief for [[Achilles]]' loss of [[Patroclus]].<ref>Homer. ''[[Iliad]]'', XVIII.</ref> This name is used to describe a [[genus]] of plants in the family [[Lythraceae]].

