'''Sweet chestnut of Ovacık village''' ({{lang-tr|Ovacık Köyü Anadolu Kestanesi}}) is a very old chestnut tree in [[Izmir Province]], western Turkey.  It is a registered [[List of natural monuments of Turkey|natural monument]] of the country.

The chestnut tree is located at Ovacık Highland close to [[Ovacık, Bayındır|Ovacık]] village in [[Bayındır]] district of Izmir Province. It is a sweet chestnut (''[[Castanea sativa]]''). The tree is {{convert|18|m|ft|abbr=on}} high, has a circumference of {{convert|8.70|m|ft|abbr=on}} at {{convert|2.80|m|ft|abbr=on}} diameter. Its age is dated to be about 500 years old.<ref name="tz"/>

The tree was registered a [[natural monument]] on February 21, 1995. The protected area of the plant covers {{convert|2500|m2|sqft|abbr=on}}.<ref name="tz"/><ref name="mp"/>

